Unnamed: 30: ﻿There are two churches listed in the almanac for the Buffalo Creek area. One of them is not named, and just says 'Buffaloe Creek,' the other is called 'B.V. Nativity' here. I suspect that the Buffaloe Creek entry is referring to something further up the creek, back into the woods north of Freeport, where the church St. Mary's is. Based on the church history given on the St. Mary's (freeport) site, I'm inclined to think that the B.V. Nativity means Blessed Virgin of the Nativity (i.e., Mary). For that reason I'm leaving this Buffaloe Creek entry empty and giving the ID to the church explicity named later on.

Unnamed: 30: ﻿This city is in Ohio and, from what I can tell, has never been part of PA, where it appears in the 1833 alamanac. My read on this is that, due to it being in eastern Ohio, closer to Cleveland (which is not yet in this almanac), it was categorized under PA because it was one of their outerlying served areas. For this reason, I've given it a Cleveland ID, as the city appears in the later 1860/70s almanacs.
